<p>I have string like <code>**some text here** and **other text here** and **next text**</code> and I want to replace it to <code>&lt;strong&gt;some text here &lt;/strong&gt;</code>. I want to replace it only when every <code>**</code> has a pair.  for example:  <code>**some text**</code> will be replaced with <code>&lt;strong&gt;some text&lt;/strong&gt;</code> but <code>**some text</code> won't be replaced. How to do this?</p>  <p>quick lesson about regex and the answer was: <code>preg_replace('/\*\*([^\*]+)(\*\*)/', '&lt;strong&gt;\1&lt;/strong&gt;', '**some text here** and **other text here** and **next text**');</code></p>